            <commentid>10211</commentid>
            <who name="Daniel Wagner">daniel.wagner</who>
            <bug_when>2009-05-28 18:27:55 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>That&#39;s a good point. I filed this report because someone on the mailing list wanted to create an app that could be used without the mouse, which is an important feature to have. But I just realized there&#39;s another way to achieve this: One could define a command with a keyboard shortcut that calls the open method of the menu button. 
Once the menu is opened, the user can move around it (and adjacent menus) just like in Windows/Linux (probably OSX, too, can&#39;t check) when you press Alt+F to open the &quot;File&quot; menu in an app.

So I guess we can set this to WONTFIX?</thetext>
